<F P=100> Palestinian Affairs </F>
<H3> <TI>   'Arafat Receives Argentine Foreign Minister </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    'Arafat Receives Argentine Foreign Minister </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1304182994 Algiers Voice of Palestine in Arabic 1702 GMT 
13 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1304182994 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Voice of Palestine </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother president Abu-'Ammar [Yasir 'Arafat] 
yesterday evening received Mr. Guido di Tella, Argentine foreign 
minister. The minister conveyed to brother Abu-'Ammar the 
greetings of Mr. Carlos Menem, president of Argentina. 
  During this meeting, they reviewed the latest developments 
in 
the Palestinian-Israeli negotiations. Brother president 
Abu-'Ammar highlighted the dangers of Israel's resorting to 
procrastination and delay, and failure to abide by the times 
agreed upon for the implementation [of the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement] -- particularly since today is 13 April -- and the 
resulting serious repercussions on the whole peace process. 
  During the meeting, they also discussed issues of mutual 
interest to the two countries. The minister gave the brother 
president a message containing the Argentine Government's 
decision to open up Palestinian representation in Buenos Aires. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

