<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Campaign To End al-'Aqabah Blockade To Be Launched </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Campaign To End al-'Aqabah Blockade To Be Launched </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1404121594 Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' in Arabic 14 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1404121594 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHBAR AL-USBU' </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] AKHBAR AL-USBU' has learned that Jordan will shortly 
make large-scale political moves, to be spearheaded by His 
Majesty King Husayn, to explain Jordan's position toward the 
international embargo imposed against the Port of al-'Aqabah and 
Iraq. Jordan's drive aims to enlighten the world community 
about the need to apply pressures to end this embargo, which is 
harmful to both Jordan and Iraq, particularly since the outlets 
of the countries neighboring Iraq are wide open to trade with 
Iraq, whereas only Jordan is besieged in this regard. Jordan is 
next only to Iraq in terms of the harm caused by this embargo. 
  Responsible Jordanian sources said that the Jordanian moves 
will take the form of royal visits abroad, the dispatch of 
envoys carrying royal messages abroad, as well as extensive 
diplomatic efforts on the international scene to be led by 
Jordanian Embassies abroad. 
  The Jordanian campaign aims to end the blockade clamped on 
the Port of al-'Aqabah and the embargo imposed on the Iraqi 
people. Lately, Jordanian-Iraqi contacts have been activated. 
Iraqi Culture and Information Minister Hamid Yusuf Hammadi, who 
is currently visiting Jordan, has relayed a message from 
President Saddam to His Majesty King Husayn. Meanwhile, Deputy 
Prime Minister Dr. Sa'id al-Tall is visiting Baghdad, where he 
has met with several Iraqi officials. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

