<H3> <TI>   Timing of Iraqi Opposition Meeting in Amman Noted </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Timing of Iraqi Opposition Meeting in Amman Noted </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1304145094 Amman AKHIR KHABAR in Arabic 11-12 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1304145094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AKHIR KHABAR </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Unattributed report: "As al-Tall Continues His Visit to </F>
Iraq, Attempts To Mar the Jordanian-Iraqi Relations"] 
  [Text] Amman--AKHIR KHABAR--It has been reported that some 
Iraqi opposition members met in Amman in March. Husayn 
al-Hakim, an Iraqi opposition leader, took part in that meeting. 
  AKHIR KHABAR has noticed that reports of that meeting were 
leaked at a time coinciding with the visit of Dr. Sa'id al-Tall, 
Jordanian deputy prime minister and minister of higher 
education, to Baghdad to brief the Iraqi brothers on the latest 
developments in the siege imposed on Iraq and al-'Aqabah. 
  The reports came on the heels of a successful recent visit 
to 
Baghdad by a Jordanian parliamentary delegation. Informed 
sources said the Iraqi leadership welcomed the delegation's 
proposal that multilateral parliamentary delegations should 
visit the big powers in order to support the Iraqi position on 
the blockade. The Iraqi National Assembly (parliament) has 
issued a statement praising Jordan's stand on the official and 
popular levels. 

</TEXT>

