<F P=102>   JN1404142394 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 
1200 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1404142394 </F>
<F P=104>  Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Brother Lieutenant General 'Ali 'Abdallah Salih, 
chairman of the Presidential Council, today received Hamid Yusuf 
Hammadi, Iraqi minister of culture and information and envoy of 
Iraqi President Saddam Husayn. 
  Hammadi conveyed to the brother Presidential Council 
chairman 
a message from his brother President Saddam Husayn dealing with 
the fraternal bilateral relations and issues of interest to our 
Arab nation. The message also dealt with the suffering of the 
sisterly Iraqi people as a result of the economic blockade 
imposed on Iraq, which requires a pan-Arab position to mitigate 
this hard human suffering of the Iraqi children, youths, and old 
people due to the continued blockade, especially since Iraq has 
stressed its commitment to all UN resolutions, led by Resolution 
687. 
  The brother chairman expressed our Yemeni people's 
solidarity 
with the fraternal Iraqi people's suffering as a result of the 
blockade. He asked the Iraqi culture and information ministers 
to convey his greetings to his brother President Saddam Husayn 
and his wishes of further progress and prosperity for the Iraqi 
people. 
  The meeting was attended by Information Minister brother 
Hasan Ahmad al-Lawzi and Dr. Muhsin Khalil, Iraqi ambassador to 
our country. 

