<F P=100> LEBANON </F>
<H3> <TI>   Israeli Shelling, Reinforcements Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Shelling, Reinforcements Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1504095194 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 0900 GMT 15 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1504095194 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The villages of Qabrikha, Majdal Silm, Tulin, and 
al-Suwwanah came under a concentrated Israel artillery barrage 
this morning. The shelling continued intermittently at the rate 
of one round per minute until 0500 today, prompting residents 
inhabitants to seek protection in shelters and the innermost 
rooms of their homes. The bombardment was accompanied by 
intensive overflights by Israeli helicopters, which fired flares 
and raked the area. Retaliating for the continuing enemy acts of 
aggression, which left three dead and dozens wounded in Sidon, 
resistance groups shelled several Israeli settlements, 
concentrating on the Galilee panhandle. The enemy admitted that 
rockets landed in the area but denied any casualties. 
  The Israeli enemy sent in many vehicles and reinforcements, 
which were spotted traveling along the international highway 
near Tallat al-'Abbad. These reinforcements have deployed in 
the al-Tayyibah- al-Qantarah-'Alman triangle. 

</TEXT>

