<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Iranian Speaker Comments on Talks With Leaders </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Iranian Speaker Comments on Talks With Leaders </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1404144694 Islamabad PTV Television Network in English 
1400 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1404144694 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad PTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Speaker of the Islamic Consultative Assembly of 
Iran, Hojjat ol-Eslam 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri, has described his 
talks with the Pakistani leaders as very useful and constructive 
with more emphasis on strengthening the role of the ECO 
[Economic Cooperation Organization]. Speaking at a news 
conference in Karachi today before his departure, the Iranian 
speaker expressed complete satisfaction on the talks he held 
with the Pakistani leaders on matters of bilateral interest 
including Kashmir, Bosnia, and the Palestine. He said the two 
sides also discussed the project of constructing a gas pipeline 
from Iran to Pakistan and setting up of an oil refinery in 
Karachi. Hojjat ol-Eslam 'Ali Akbar Nateq-Nuri said the two 
countries will shortly exchange delegations for carrying out the 
feasibility for the proposed project. Replying to a question, 
he said the pace of cooperation among the ECO member countries 
would accelerate with the passage of time. 

</TEXT>

