<H3> <TI>   Vietnamese Deputy Foreign Minister Meets Velayati </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Vietnamese Deputy Foreign Minister Meets Velayati </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1404193794 Tehran IRNA in English 1429 GMT 14 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1404193794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 14, IRNA -- The visiting Vietnamese 
deputy foreign minister, Nguyen Dy Nien here today called for 
expansion of Tehran-Hanoi cooperation in the international 
forums. 
  In a meeting with Foreign Minister 'Ali Akbar Velayati, he 
expressed the satisfaction of Vietnam's high-ranking officials 
with expansion of relations with Tehran and hoped that the 
foundations of direct relations between the two countries would 
strengthen with the imminent visit of Vietnam's president to 
Tehran. 
  Velayati in response referred to the historical background 
of 
Vietnamese people against the occupiers and domineering powers 
and said that Iran attached special importance to its relations 
with Hanoi. 
  He voiced Iran's readiness to host the Vitenamese president 
and hoped that the visit would have positive and fruitful 
results in expansion of bilateral relations. 
  Nien will deliver a message from Vietnam's president to 
President Hashemi-Rafsanjani. 

</TEXT>

