of Egypt appeals to all Rwandan parties to exercise 
self-restraint, accept an immediate cease-fire, and create the 
appropriate conditions for relief organizations to carry out 
their humanitarian mission. It also urges these parties to 
immediately resume their efforts to implement the Arosha 
Agreement so as to attain stability and peace in the country. 
  The Egyptian ambassador and Embassy staff in Kigali have 
been 
instructed to leave Rwanda temporarily in light of the dangers 
they are facing there and the extreme deterioration in security. 

