<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Protests Against GATT Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Protests Against GATT Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1504095294 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 0830 
GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1504095294 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In the Pondicherry assembly, the entire opposition 
consisting of the AIADMK [All India Anna Dravida Munnetra 
Kazhagam], DMK [Dravida Munnetra Kazhagam], CPI [Communist Party 
of India], and Janata Dal staged a walkout today following the 
deputy speaker's refusal to admit an adjournment motion. The 
motion tabled by CPI and Janata Dal members sought to discuss 
the signing of the GATT agreement. The deputy speaker, Mr. A.B. 
Subramaniam, while refusing permission for the motion said that 
the subject does not come under the purview of the union 
territory's assembly. The lone CPI member attended the session 
with a black towel on his shoulders to protest the signing of 
the GATT accord today. 
  In Kerala, the 12-hour statewide bundh [strike] called by 
the 
CPI-ML [Communist Party of India-Marxist Leninist] today evoked 
little response. Barring some minor incidents of stone 
throwing, the bundh was by and large peaceful. Some shops and 
business establishments remained closed. However, traffic plied 
as usual. The bundh call was given in protest against India 
signing the GATT agreement. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

