BFN 

  [Text] Majles Speaker Nateq-Nuri arrived in the Sri Lankan 
capital Colombo from Pakistan last night on the second leg of 
his Asian tour and was greeted by the Sri Lankan speaker and 
Iranians living there. During his stay in Sri Lanka, the Majles 
speaker will meet high-ranking Sri Lankan officials and will 
discuss issues of mutual interest. 
  Sri Lanka, which is situated in south Asia, has a population 
of 17 million. Its most important export item is tea. 

