<F P=100> ISRAEL </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Detain 17 Hamas Activists in Strip </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Detain 17 Hamas Activists in Strip </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1404185094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1700 GMT 14 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1404185094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The security forces have detained two Hamas 
[Islamic Resistance Movement] leaders from the Gaza Strip -- 
Nidal Ruhani and Ghassan al-Siyam -- and fifteen activists from 
'Izz-al-Din al- Qassam, the military arm of Hamas. 
  Our correspondent Moti Amir reports that in an operation in 
the al-Shati' refugee camp and Gaza city, which lasted several 
days and nights, the security forces detained Nidal Ruhani and 
Ghassan al-Siyam, and 15 more Hamas members were detained in the 
course of the two men's interrogation. Following a search of 
their homes, large sums of money, documents, and other materiel 
were seized, and it was learned that they were key elements in 
the Hamas operations against the security forces in the Strip. 
  Brigadier General Doron Almog, the IDF [Israel Defense 
Forces] commander in the Gaza Strip, commended the Shin Bet 
personnel and the other security forces for the capture of the 
Hamas members. 

</TEXT>

