BFN 

  [Text] The Social Liberal Party today announced its 
participation in the Transitional National Council [interim 
parliament]. The party indicated that it regarded its 
participation as a duty for the preservation of public interest. 
For its part, the Workers' Party has announced that it would 
not take part in the Transitional National Council that is to be 
set up at the end of this month. It justified its decision by 
the fact that it did not attend the National Dialogue Conference. 

