<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Round of PLO-Israeli Talks Begins in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Round of PLO-Israeli Talks Begins in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th on Delay of Return of Palestinians </H4>

<F P=102> NC1804055694 Paris AFP in English 0240 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1804055694 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, April 18 (AFP)--The return of around 50 
banned or wanted Palestinians to the occupied territories, 
scheduled for Sunday [17 April], has been delayed by 
formalities, the Palestinian chief negotiator Nabil Sha'th said 
late Sunday. 
  The difficulties are being resolved and the exiles could be 
brought together in Egypt or Jordan Monday from where they could 
be transferred to the Gaza Strip and the West Bank, Sha'th told 
reporters here. 
  The delay resulted from the fact that Palestinians who were 
outside Jordan and Egypt needed to gain visas for the two 
countries, said Sha'th, who is leading negotiations with Israel 
on Palestinian self-rule on the Gaza Strip and in the West Bank 
town of Jericho. 
  An official from PLO leader Yasir 'Arafat's Fatah 
organisation said 17 out of the 50 Palestinians would have gone 
to Gaza from Egypt Sunday but for the technical problems. 
  A first group of 50 banned Palestinians returned to the 
occupied territories on April 5. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

