<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Multilateral Talks on Water Begin in Oman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Multilateral Talks on Water Begin in Oman </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israeli Delegation Arrives </H4>

<F P=102> TA1504154094 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in English 1500 GMT 15 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1504154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Israeli delegation for the multilateral talks 
on water has arrived in Oman. They were greeted by Omani 
Foreign Ministry officials. The talks are due to get under way 
on Sunday [17 April]. The Israeli delegation is headed by Deputy 
Foreign Minister Yosi Beilin, who is expected to meet with 
senior Omani officials during his stay. 
  Beilin said on his arrival that the visit is important 
because it broadens Israel's horizons, enabling the country to 
reach new areas. 
  The Israeli team flew to Muscat on an Egyptian plane from 
Cairo and not on a direct flight from Israel. 

</TEXT>

