<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Multilateral Talks on Water Begin in Oman </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Multilateral Talks on Water Begin in Oman </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Israel, Oman Reach Accord on Solar Energy </H4>

<F P=102> TA1804062294 Tel Aviv IDF Radio in Hebrew 0500 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> TA1804062294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv IDF Radio </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Aharon Barne'a from Oman] </F>
  [Text] Addressing the multilateral water talks yesterday, 
Omani Foreign Minister Yusuf Bin-'Alawi said that it is time to 
stop emphasizing the very fact that the conference is being held 
and to start acting. Thus, a mere few hours later, the Israeli 
delegation and the Omanis reached an agreement -- the first of 
its kind -- on regional Omani-Israeli cooperation in solar 
energy development. Israeli experts will visit an Omani solar 
energy center in about two weeks, and Omani solar energy experts 
will visit Israel several weeks later to promote the issue. 
Thus, Omani-Israeli cooperation on solar energy is to be 
launched in the coming weeks. 
  So far, all the Israeli proposals at the multilateral talks 
have been submitted through third parties, but today Israel 
itself will submit a proposal on a project for sea water 
desalination for small towns. 

</TEXT>

