<H3> <TI>   League Delegate Calls Israel's Stance `False' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    League Delegate Calls Israel's Stance `False' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1704150594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1240 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1704150594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 17 Apr (MENA)--Arab League Secretary General 
Dr. 'Ismat 'Abd-al-Majid today received Nayif Sa'ud al-Qadi, 
Jordan's ambassador in Cairo and permanent delegate to the Arab 
League. 
  Ambassador al-Qadi stated afterward that he briefed Dr. 
'Abd-al-Majid on Jordan's true stance on the peace process. He 
described the Israeli stance as false, noting that the intention 
is to pressure Jordan. 
  He added that he conveyed to the Arab League secretary 
general the text of the Jordanian cabinet's statement on the 
(?latest) Israeli (?statements). 

