<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-13084 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes074_r_94006" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-074 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  18 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Officials, Parties React to Signing of GATT Accord </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Minister `Strongly' Defends GATT Accord </H4>

<F P=102> BK1804130494 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1804130494 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The commerce minister has strongly justified India 
signing the new GATT deal, saying the opposition stand is based 
on narrow partisan considerations. Mr. Pranab Mukherji, who 
returned to New Delhi from Marrakesh this morning, said there is 
no rationale in the demand for opting out of the global trading 
system. He pointed out that 20 more countries want to join the 
new trade agreement in addition to the 125 countries which are 
signatories to it. 

</TEXT>

