<F P=100> Pakistan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Defense Minister Discusses Nuclear Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Minister Discusses Nuclear Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1704121994 Islamabad THE NATION in English 17 Apr 94 p 12 </F>
<F P=103> BK1704121994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad THE NATION </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Sukkur (NNI) -- Federal Minister for Defence Aftab 
Shaban Mirani has said that Pakistan does not intend to build 
the nuclear bomb but, at the same, we would never disband our 
muclear programme. 
  Talking informally to newsmen at his residence here on 
Saturday, he strongly refuted speculations that any deal had 
been struck with the US on the issue. 
  He said Pakistan would never accept outside pressure on a 
matter related to our country's national security. 
  He blamed the Opposition's negative role in playing up the 
issue as "childish". 
  He also categorically ruled out reduction in the national 
defence budget and added "We had a traditionally aggressive 
enemy on our borders which had exploded a nuclear device as far 
back as 20 years ago and was only increasing its defence 
budget". "How can we ignore this build up?, he asked. [no end 
quotes as published] 
  He said that Pakistan would continue to strive for declaring 
our region as a nuclear-free zone. 

</TEXT>

