<H3> <TI>   Danish Defense Forces Chief Visits Kashmir Control Line </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Danish Defense Forces Chief Visits Kashmir Control Line </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1604091994 Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network in Urdu 0200 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1604091994 </F>
<F P=104>  Islamabad Radio Pakistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Urdu </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Denmark's defense forces chief, General (Jorgen 
Maine), who visited (Pando) Post along the Line of Control [LOC] 
in Azad Kashmir, was briefed on the situation in occupied 
Kashmir and the increasing violations of the LOC by Indian 
forces. He was accompanied by General Shamim Alam Khan, 
chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff Committee. The Danish 
general was also apprised of the large-scale violation of human 
rights at the hands of the Indian forces in occupied Kashmir. 
He was told that infamous laws have been enforced in occupied 
Kashmir, under which the Kashmiris have been deprived of their 
basic rights. The Indian judiciary is not allowed to hear any 
case relating to any crime committed by the Indian forces 
against the Kashmiris. The Danish general was also informed 
that India has deployed a large number of troops along the LOC 
to prevent the helpless refugees from coming into Pakistan from 
India. He was also told about the unprovoked violation of the 
cease-fire, as a result of which civilians living along the LOC 
are being killed. The Danish general also attended a briefing 
at the field station of the UN observers in Muzaffarabad. 

</TEXT>

