<H3> <TI>   Israeli Mock Raids, Shelling Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Israeli Mock Raids, Shelling Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1704161694 Beirut Radio Lebanon in Arabic 1530 GMT 17 Apr 
94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1704161694 </F>
<F P=104>  Beirut Radio Lebanon </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israeli warplanes staged several sorties over the 
south this morning, specifically over the al-Nabatiyah and the 
Iqlim al-Tuffah areas. They staged two mock raids at low 
altitude and broke the sound barrier. 
  The eastern hills and the outskirts of Kafr Rumman came 
under 
heavy machine-gun fire at 0800 today from the Israeli forces' 
positions in al-Dabshah. 
  In the central sector, the outskirts of the town of Yatar 
came under intensive machine-gun fire at midnight last night 
while the sky overhead was lit by flares. 
  In the Marj 'Uyun area, an agent Lahd [South Lebanese Army] 
unit combed with machine-gun fire the main road that links Marj 
'Uyun with the Zumarayya crossing point and that passes through 
the al-Khiyan junction and the Nab' al-Hasbani. 
  According to information received from the occupied strip, 
the SLA command interrogated a number of its members following 
the explosion of a device under one of its patrols at the 
entrance to Marj 'Uyun three days ago. The explosion killed 
recruit Faris Ilyas Jabbur from Kawkaba and injured another. 

</TEXT>

