<H3> <TI>   Envoy Leaves for Yemen With Messages for Salih, al-Bid </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Envoy Leaves for Yemen With Messages for Salih, al-Bid </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1704120394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1120 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1704120394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 17 Apr (MENA)--Ambassador Badr Hamman, 
assistant foreign minister for Arab affairs, left Cairo for 
Sanaa as President Mubarak's special envoy this afternoon. He 
will deliver two messages to Yemeni President 'Ali 'Abdallah 
Salih and Vice President 'Ali Salim al-Bid, secretary general of 
the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP]. 
  Ambassador Hammam said before leaving that the two messages 
deal with Egyptian-Yemeni relations and the Egyptian view of the 
Yemeni situation and stress the need for cooperation among all 
the Yemeni parties to surmount the situation in the country. 
  Hammam pointed out that his mission in Yemen falls within 
the 
context of the continuing Egyptian role of helping brother 
Yemenis overcome the situation the country has been encountering 
since last August. This role also seeks to preserve Yemeni 
unity and implement the pledge and accord document approved and 
signed by all the political parties in the Jordanian capital, 
Amman, on 20 February, he explained. 
  The Egyptian official added: We are confident that the 
political leaders in Yemen know of their responsibility to 
foster and maintain unity. We will cooperate together to 
achieve the collective goal of all the Yemeni parties, he said, 
adding: We will try to provide favorable conditions and common 
ground for bringing the parties together to overcome the crisis. 

</TEXT>

