<H3> <TI>   Discusses Relations With Wali </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Relations With Wali </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1704155294 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1430 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1704155294 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 17 Apr (MENA)--Dr. Yusuf Wali, deputy prime 
minister and minister of agriculture and land reclamation, met 
today with Ugandan Vice President Dr. Samson Kisekka and the 
delegation accompanying him who are currently visiting Cairo. 
  They reviewed a number of issues of mutual interest, 
primarily the current situation in Africa. 
  During the meeting, Dr. Wali emphasized the firm relations 
between the two countries and Egypt's readiness to supply Uganda 
with Egyptian agricultural products, especially cotton and oil 
products. Wali also agreed to increase scholarships for 
Ugandans at the Egyptian international agricultural center. 
  The Ugandan official said his country looks forward to 
enhancing bilateral ties and economic and agricultural 
cooperation with Egypt. 
  The Ugandan official is expected to meet several officials 
and visit major agricultural and industrial projects. 

</TEXT>

