<H3> <TI>   Campaign Launched in Cairo, Asyut Against Fugitives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Campaign Launched in Cairo, Asyut Against Fugitives </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Convicts Captured in Cairo </H4>

<F P=102> NC1604180594 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1610 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1604180594 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 16 Apr (MENA)--The security service in 
western Cairo has launched a campaign in shanty towns and remote 
areas in the past two days to capture fugitive criminals and 
escaped convicts. 
  Major General Mahmud Wajdi, director of the Cairo General 
Detective Department, has stated that the campaigns resulted in 
the seizure of 66 firearms, persons involved in 26 drug cases, 
296 suspects in political cases, and 12 fugitive convicts. He 
said that 410 cases of individual gangs and another three-member 
gang specializing in car robbery have been uncovered. 
  As for the political suspects, Wajdi said the arrested 296 
persons are being checked to determine whether they belong to 
extremist groups. 
  Maj. Gen. Wajdi added that campaigns that covered northern 
Cairo have unveiled 29 cases of narcotics and 11 criminal cases 
and have seized five firearms. 
  During these last campaigns, nine persons suspected of 
illegal political activity and 125 fugitive convicts were 
captured. 
  Maj. Gen. Wajdi pointed out that the campaigns started two 
days ago in various sectors in Cairo at the instructions of 
Interior Minister Hasan al-Alfi. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

