<F P=100> Egypt </F>
<H3> <TI>   Campaign Launched in Cairo, Asyut Against Fugitives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Campaign Launched in Cairo, Asyut Against Fugitives </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Fugitives, `Terrorists' Arrested in Asyut </H4>

<F P=102> NC1604161394 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1520 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1604161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Asyut, Upper Egypt, 16 Apr (MENA)--The centers and 
villages of Asyut Governorate have been the scene of intensified 
security sweeps to arrest escaped criminals and terrorists. 
  Asyut Security Chief Major General Majdi al-Basyuni has said 
that the sweeps, which started early this morning and covered 
remote and shanty towns, resulted in catching 28 terrorists 
wanted in connection with various cases. 
  Maj. Gen. al-Basyuni added that these terrorists included 
nine in the city of Asyut and surrounding villages and urban 
centers, eight in al-Qusiyah, six in the city of Manfalut, two 
in al-Badari, two in Abu Tij, and two in al-Ghana'im. 
  The sweeps involved the State Security Detectives, Central 
Security, regular troops, the police, and Public Security 
forces. A total of 10 weapons--two automatic rifles, five 
pistols, and three rifles of various types--were seized during 
the sweeps. 
  The teams involved in the sweeps arrested 197 persons on 
suspicion of illegal political activity, who are being 
interrogated, and 141 fugitive convicts. 
  To facilitate full security control of the governorate, 
Asyut 
was recently divided into four security zones. Each zone is 
headed by an assistant security chief. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

