<F P=100> SYRIA </F>
<H3> <TI>   Al-Kasm, al-Shar' Confer With UN Fact-Finding Mission </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Kasm, al-Shar' Confer With UN Fact-Finding Mission </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1604154094 Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network in 
Arabic 1415 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1604154094 </F>
<F P=104>  Damascus Syrian Arab Republic Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dr. 'Abd-al-Ra'uf al-Kasm, head of the National 
Security Office, at 1300 today received the UN Middle East 
fact-finding mission that comprises a number of journalists from 
various world countries. 
  Dr. al-Kasm answered journalists' questions concerning 
developments in the peace process and the Arab-Israeli conflict. 
He emphasized the constants of Syrian Arab policy, and its 
position on the just and comprehensive peace in the Middle East. 
  This morning, Foreign Minister Faruq al-Shar' received the 
mission, which includes ranking Western and Japanese media men. 
The foreign minister answered their questions and said Israel 
intransigence since the beginning of the peace process 
obstructed the realization of substantial progress in the peace 
process. Al- Shar' said the opportunity for peace is getting 
narrower day by day because of Israel's insistence on continuing 
its occupation of the Arab territories, contrary to the UN 
resolutions on which the peace process was based. 
  The foreign minister expressed Syria's determination to 
continue its objectives, which are identical with the 
international community's objectives, to realize a just and 
comprehensive peace in the region, in accordance with the Madrid 
formula. He stressed the importance of the objective role of 
mass media in the international arena in distinguishing between 
those who want real, just, and comprehensive peace, and those 
who block this peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

