<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Senate Supports King's Position on Israeli Charges </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Senate Supports King's Position on Israeli Charges </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1704141794 Amman Radio Jordan Network in Arabic 1300 GMT 
17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1704141794 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Radio Jordan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In its meeting held today under Senate President 
Ahmad al-Lawzi, the Senate issued a statement expressing support 
for His Majesty King Husayn's statements to the local and 
foreign media. 
  The Senate's statement said his majesty has reiterated the 
constants of the firm Jordanian policy toward the Palestine 
question and the issues and problems resulting from it. 
  The Senate expressed full support for the Jordanian 
position, 
which was expressed by his majesty when he clearly explained 
Jordan's sincere intentions toward a just peace that realizes 
the national ambitions of the Palestinian people on their soil 
and liberates the occupied Arab territories in harmony with 
international legitimacy and human rights. 
  The Senate emphasized that Jordan has always stood against 
terrorism and has paid a dear price with the blood of its sons 
while firmly confronting terrorism. Jordan has always been 
eager to reject violence in politics. This position is 
manifested in Jordan's long history of working for the cause of 
just peace. 
  The Senate also stressed that Jordan strongly rejects any 
charges that it is soft on, or encourages terrorism. It 
considers that these false charges are made to justify the 
aggressive pressure being placed on the country, including the 
unjust siege on the Port of al-'Aqabah, in a bid to force it to 
change its pan-Arab constructive position on just and lasting 
peace. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

