<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Papers Reject Israeli `Allegations' of Hamas Support </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papers Reject Israeli `Allegations' of Hamas Support </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    `Chain of Pressure' Seen </H4>

<F P=102> JN1604083494 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 16 Apr 94 pp 1, 25 </F>
<F P=103> JN1604083494 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Editorial: "False and Rejected Allegations!"] </F>
  [Text] Following the fedayeen operations carried out by 
Palestinian citizens inside the "green line" in 'Afula and 
Hadera in reply to the massacre at the holy al-Ibrahimi Mosque 
in Hebron, the leaders of Israel have begun to utter threats and 
level accusations indiscriminately. The most recent threats 
were uttered by Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin and Foreign 
Minister Shim'on Peres, who accused Jordan of allowing the free 
movement of Hamas [the Islamic Resistance Movement] on Jordanian 
territory. They also said that the official Hamas spokesman 
claimed responsibility for the 'Afula and Hadera operations! 
  It is true that a media official sympathizing with Hamas has 
boastfully claimed responsibility for these operations. 
However, the real announcement about this responsibility came 
first from loudspeakers in the Abu-Khudayr Mosque and other 
mosques in Gaza. Thus, Israel's allegations that Jordan allows 
freedom of movement for Hamas--only because a media official 
claimed responsibility for the two operations--are false and 
rejected allegations. The threats uttered by the Israeli prime 
minister and foreign minister are only one link in the chain of 
pressure and blackmail pursued by the Israeli leadership 
whenever it feels distressed and encircled. 
  It is known to both us and Israel that Hamas has no 
political 
or military organization, nor do its members or sympathizers 
carry out activities of a military nature, outside occupied 
Palestine. The whole story is that certain sympathizers in the 
Arab countries and other countries express support for, and 
sympathy with, Hamas in the occupied territories. Moreover, 
those who carried out the 'Afula and Hadera operations were 
Palestinians from the occupied territories; they carried out the 
two operations inside Israel despite the cordon and siege 
imposed on the occupied territories. 
  Jordan, which has rejected such threats in the past and 
which 
rejects them today, will not accept this tone by the Israeli 
leadership, and will not yield to any pressure or blackmail from 
any party whatsoever. Jordan also believes that the Israeli 
leadership should realize that its procrastination concerning 
the peace process, its failure to recognize the Palestinian 
people's legitimate rights, and its failure to withdraw from the 
occupied territories are the reason and driving force for all 
acts of violence. This leadership should be aware that a just, 
comprehensive, and lasting peace would guarantee regional 
stability and entrench security. Threats and insistence on both 
occupation and aggression will only yield more bloodshed, 
victims, and violence. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-13138 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes074_m_94011" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-NES-94-074 </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  16 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Papers Reject Israeli `Allegations' of Hamas Support </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Papers Reject Israeli `Allegations' of Hamas Support </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Remarks `Do Not Scare' Country </H4>

<F P=102> JN1604095094 Amman AL-RA'Y in Arabic 16 Apr 94 p 28 </F>
<F P=103> JN1604095094 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-RA'Y </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Every Day" column by Tariq Masarwah: "Security Bankruptcy </F>
and the Failure of the Peace Game"] 
  [Text] The Rabin-Peres warnings to Jordan declare the 
failure of Israeli policies in the occupied territory. Hamas is 
not in Amman, but in 'Afula, Hadera, Gaza, Hebron, and in every 
part of Palestine. Hamas communiques are faxed, in moments, 
from Jerusalem -- which they call the eternal capital of Israel 
-- to Amman, Damascus, and London. Jordan Television broadcast 
a very brief report, no more than a minute, about the Hadera 
explosion while the Israeli radio carried for one and a half 
hours a report about the explosion and the reactions to this 
explosion. 
  These Israeli threats do not scare us; they are a 
declaration 
of the bankruptcy of the military and security occupation forces 
inside the occupied territory and an unconvincing quest for 
excuses, outside the occupied territory, to justify this 
failure. The occupation is an impasse for Rabin and Peres, not 
for Jordan. Violent resistance against occupation has exposed 
the game of peace, and turned the doves of the Labor Party -- 
who preach about the prosperity that will be achieved in the 
region once the Middle East market is established -- into hawks 
who make threats against others. Violent resistance has also who 
turned carriers of olive branches into pilots of lethal U.S. 
aircraft. They want the game to play in accordance with their 
own rules and, if it deviates from this course, war will be the 
alternative. 
  We say these ridiculous Israeli threats will not scare us. 
We will put them in our political calculations together with 
the U.S. siege on al-'Aqabah. 
  We know that the U.S. Embassy [in Amman] has been working, 
since the 'Afula incident, to mobilize public opinion against 
two youths who carry Hamas faxes to the Jordanian media just as 
Arab journalists in London carry Hamas faxes to AL-SHARQ 
AL-AWSAT, AL- HAYAH, AL-QUDS AL-DUWALI, and AL-AHRAM AL-DUWALI. 
Hamas communiques reach us as they reach every part in the 
world. 
  The Labor Party doves, who turned into hawks, and peace 
advocates who turned into warmongers, have reached a deadlock 
and the game of peace has deviated from its course and has been 
exposed. And Jordan is not responsible for this. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

