First Program Network in Persian 0930 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704115094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In today's open session of the Majles, Mr. Rohani, 
the deputy speaker of the Islamic Consultative Majles described 
the onslaught of the Serbs against Gorazde as yet more evidence 
of the lies and deceit of international circles and the United 
Nations. He condemned the silence and time-wasting of the 
Security Council in response to the Serbs' aggression and said: 
Of all the resolutions passed by this council, only the 
resolution imposing an arms embargo on the Muslims of 
Bosnia-Herzegovina is being implemented. This in itself 
encourages the Serbs to further carry on with their aggression 
and blood shedding. 
  On the downing of two U.S. helicopters by the fighters of 
the 
same country in northern Iraq, he said that this would lead to 
instability and insecurity for all the countries of the region 
and added that the downing was a result of America's domineering 
policies. 

</TEXT>

