<F P=103> LD1704132794 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 17, IRNA -- Ukrainian Foreign Minister 
Anatoliy Zlenko, arrived here Sunday at the head of a high 
ranking politico-economic delegation on a three-day official 
visit. 
  Zlenko, who is carrying a message from Ukrainian President 
Leonid Kravchuk for President Akbar Hashemi-Rafsanjani, was 
greeted at Tehran airport by his Iranian counterpart 'Ali Akbar 
Velayati. 
  Talking to reporters upon his arrival, Zlenko, said he was 
here to further expand bilateral relations in various fields. 
  Zlenko said his visit provided a good opportunity for talks 
with Iranian officials on ways of consolidating and promoting 
bilateral relations and on issues of mutual interest. 

</TEXT>

