  [Text] Four Israelis were wounded in the Jerusalem attack. 
One sustained serious wounds and three sustained light injuries. 
Our police affairs correspondent Aviv Bushinsky reports that a 
17-year-old Arab from East Jerusalem got on the bus in the Neve 
Ya'aqov neighborhood and attacked passengers with an ax. He was 
shot by an IDF [Israel Defense Forces] soldier, wounded, and 
captured. Our correspondent Ofra Nehmad reports that two of the 
casualties were wounded by shots fired by the soldier. The 
wounded were taken to Hadassah-'En Kerem Hospital. An 
unidentified man called Qol Yisra'el's Arabic Department to 
announce that the terrorist belonged to Hamas [Islamic 
Resistance Movement]. 
  Prime Minister Yitzhaq Rabin said that there is a reasonable 
chance to conclude the negotiations with the PLO within several 
weeks. Rabin told a meeting of the coalition's Knesset factions 
that the evacuation from Gaza and Jericho will be short and will 
last two to three weeks. He stressed that Israel will not agree 
to the PLO continuing in the peace talks and at the same time 
reaching agreements with Hamas on attacks inside Israel. For 
us, that is the red line, the prime minister said. He noted 
that Israel acted in Cairo and in other places to foil such an 
agreement and will judge developments by results on the ground. 

</TEXT>

