<H3> <TI>   Cabinet To Warn PLO on Cooperation With Hamas </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cabinet To Warn PLO on Cooperation With Hamas </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704113394 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1100 GMT 17 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704113394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The cabinet today decided to warn the PLO against 
cooperating with Hamas [Islamic Resistance Movement], in the 
wake of reports on possible cooperation between the two 
organizations. This was reported at the close of the weekly 
cabinet session. Our political correspondent Shlomo Raz reports 
that the cabinet approved the issuance of 20,000 work permits 
for Palestinians, mainly in farming. The laborers will be 35 
years old, or above. The cabinet also approved the allocation 
of 30 million shekels for government-initiated projects and 
social welfare payments for the Palestinians in the territories. 
For the time being, the closure will continue indefinitely. 
  Knesset Member Ori Or, chairman of the Knesset Foreign 
Affairs and Defense Committee, said today that the cooperation 
announced by Hamas and Fatah in the territories is not an 
agreement between the leadership of the two organizations. 
These are understandings made by local Gaza activists. The 
understandings were made because some Hamas members are hoping 
for jobs in the autonomy administration, and in view of the 
interest shared by both organizations to prevent bloodshed in 
Gaza. Ori Or further said that there are serious difference 
among Hamas members. Activists in the territories claim that 
they should take part in the PLO administration in order to 
survive when autonomy is established. At the same time, some of 
the organization leaders believe that terror is the only path to 
be pursued. 
  Likud has called on the prime minister to stop negotiations 
with the PLO if it does not immediately stop cooperating with 
Hamas. Likud faction chairman Moshe Qatzav stated it is now 
clear that the working assumption of the Oslo agreement, 
according to which the PLO would fight Hamas, is silly. 

</TEXT>

