<H3> <TI>   Rabin Said Consulting IDF Aides on Golan Withdrawal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Rabin Said Consulting IDF Aides on Golan Withdrawal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1604173394 Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network in 
Hebrew 1700 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1604173394 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem New Channel 2 Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The prime minister has launched a series of 
consultations with senior IDF [Israel Defense Forces] elements, 
including the chief of staff and the Intelligence Branch chief, 
as to Israel's consent to withdraw on the Golan Heights. 
Intelligence Branch Chief Uri Sagi has made two trips to 
Washington recently, and one of his visits has been kept secret 
until now. 
  The meetings are part of the drafting of a working paper 
entitled The Israel-Syria Peace Package, and it outlines the 
Israeli stands on an agreement with Syria. 
  Our political correspondent 'Imanu'el Rosen reports that the 
proposal will be submitted to U.S. Secretary of State Warren 
Christopher, who is slated to arrive in the region in about 10 
days. 
  Likud elements asserted that by proposing to withdraw from 
the Golan while al-Asad-inspired katyushas are being launched at 
the Galilee, Rabin is behaving with obduracy. 

</TEXT>

