<H3> <TI>   Peres To Meet 'Arafat in Bucharest 21 Apr </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Peres To Meet 'Arafat in Bucharest 21 Apr </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1704175294 Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1704175294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Israel Television Channel 1 Network 
in Hebrew 1700 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The United States is pressuring Israel and the PLO 
to sign a Gaza-Jericho withdrawal agreement this month so that 
the signing ceremony can take place during the secretary of 
state's visit to the region in late April. 
  Our political correspondent Gadi Sukenik reports that 
Shim'on 
Peres and Yasir 'Arafat will meet several times at a conference 
in Bucharest on Thursday and Friday so as to speed up the 
negotiations. Peres will probably also meet Jordanian Prime 
Minister al-Majali there, and there are currently contacts to 
work that out. 
  The United States is demanding that Israel and Syria prepare 
a package of their demands on security, peace, and a Golan 
withdrawal prior to Secretary Christopher's visit. Due to that, 
deliberations are taking place in Rabin's and Peres' bureaus on 
various position papers. It is unclear whether the Syrians are 
working on their own proposals. 

