<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   New Round of PLO-Israeli Talks Begins in Cairo </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Round of PLO-Israeli Talks Begins in Cairo </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Sha'th Comments Before Talks </H4>

<F P=102> NC1704120994 Cairo MENA in Arabic 1130 GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> NC1704120994 </F>
<F P=104>  Cairo MENA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cairo, 17 Apr (MENA) -- The Palestinian and Israeli 
negotiators today began a new round of negotiations to overcome 
obstacles preventing the implementation of the Gaza-Jericho 
agreement for Palestinian self-rule. 
  The talks began with a separate meeting between Dr. Nabil 
Sha'th, Palestinian President Yasir 'Arafat's political adviser 
and head of the Palestinian negotiating delegation, and General 
Amnon Shahaq, deputy chief of staff and head of the Israeli 
delegation, to draw up the agenda for this round of 
negotiations, which is expected to continue until Thursday. 
  In a statement to correspondents beforehand, Dr. Sha'th 
said: 
We will do our best to make this round the last. He noted that 
they will continue to discuss the topics discussed in previous 
rounds, particularly those pertaining to security and water. 
Dr. Sha'th expressed the hope that agreement will be reached 
with the Israeli delegation on these issues. 
  Regarding the impending meeting between Palestinian 
president 
Yasir 'Arafat and Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres in 
Bucharest on Friday, Dr. Sha'th said its original purpose was 
not to try to overcome the obstacles in the current negotiations 
in Cairo. It will take place on the sidelines of the world 
economic conference, which will discuss economic cooperation in 
the Middle East in the era of peace. 
  The Security, Civilian, and Legal Affairs Committees are 
expected to meet later today. 

</TEXT>

