<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Mojahedin Capture 12 Militia Security Posts </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704192294 Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network in Pashto 1530 
GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704192294 </F>
<F P=104>  Kabul Radio Afghanistan Network </F>
<F P=105>  Pashto </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] As many as 12 hilltop security posts of the militia 
in the direction of Kayan Dara in Baghlan Province have been 
captured by the mojahedin. A responsible security source of the 
country told a military correspondent of BAKHTAR INFORMATION 
AGENCY that in a successful mopping-up operation, the mojahedin 
captured 12 militia posts in Nawbahar, Alokag, Poshtak, Debak, 
and Kataposta areas. In the operation 10 militia were killed 
and 10 others were taken prisoner. General Yaqub, a comander of 
the militia, is also among the prisoners. 
  Similarly four posts of the (?coordination council's) 
militia 
in Hassantal and the old town of Baghlan, in Baghlan Province, 
have been captured by mojahedin and forces of the Islamic army. 
A mopping-up operation in Baghlan Province to clear the Baghlan 
Province of the militia continues. 

</TEXT>

