<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Various Muslim organizations held a demonstration in 
the capital today to draw the world community's attention toward 
human rights violations in Pakistan. They also protested 
against the victimization of Urdu speaking muhajirs [Indian 
immigrants] by the Army in the Sind Province. Later, a 
delegation led by the Falah-i-Millat [Islamic Community Welfare] 
Action Committee's general secretary, Dr. Mohammad Furkan, 
submitted a memorandum to the Pakistani high commissioner urging 
upon Islamabad to stop atrocities against muhajirs and release 
the thousands of workers of the Muhajir Qaumi Movement 
languishing in jails for several years. 

