<F P=100> Libya </F>
<H3> <TI>   Withdrawal From Aouzzou Strip Reportedly Delayed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Withdrawal From Aouzzou Strip Reportedly Delayed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704011794 Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network in Arabic 
2300 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704011794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat Moroccan Kingdom Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Libya has delayed the withdrawal of its troops from 
the Aouzzou Strip over which the International Court of Justice 
had declared the sovereignty of Chad. UN sources have said that 
the withdrawal operation which was planned for 15 April has been 
delayed until tomorrow. The committee in charge of monitoring 
the withdrawal of Libyan troops from the Aouzzou Strip is formed 
of two UN teams, a military team and a civilian one. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

