<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PLO, Israeli Negotiators Continue Cairo Meetings </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Correspondent Reports `No Progress' </H4>

<F P=102> TA1804193294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1600 GMT 18 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1804193294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] No progress was made in the Cairo talks today, our 
correspondent Moti Amir reports. The Palestinians presented a 
detailed working paper on water matters, and Israeli experts 
will go to Cairo tonight to study it. Differences surfaced in 
the subcommittee on communications and following the 
intervention of the delegation heads, the Palestinians withdrew 
their demand to reopen issues already agreed upon two months ago. 
  Muhammad Dahlan told our correspondent that six deportees 
would arrive in the Gaza Strip tomorrow, and another 10 on 
Friday. He noted that there has still not been any progress on 
the release of Palestinian detainees. He said Israel now agrees 
to release only 4,000 detainees although last week it agreed to 
free 5,000. The PLO is demanding the release of 8,300 
detainees, including Hamas activists. 

</TEXT>

