<H4>    Israel Said To Agree to Detainees' Release </H4>

<F P=102> TA1904103294 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 1000 GMT 19 
Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> TA1904103294 </F>
<F P=104>  Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The negotiations between Israel and the Palestinians 
are continuing in Cairo today. Today's talks revolve around the 
release of the Palestinian detainees. A member of the 
Palestinian delegation said Israel has agreed to release all the 
detainees, including Hamas members, adding that the main 
argument revolves around the timetable for their release. 
  Our envoy in Cairo Moti Amir was told by a Palestinian 
source 
that Egypt will open a quasi-consulate in Jericho which will 
serve the residents of the Palestinian autonomous areas until an 
independent Palestinian state is established. According to the 
source, the consulate will be located in a building belonging to 
the Coptic church, upon the approval of the head of the Coptic 
church in Egypt. 

