<F P=100> INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS </F>
<F P=101> Arab-Israeli Talks </F>
<H3> <TI>   Multilateral Water Talks Continue in Muscat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Multilateral Water Talks Continue in Muscat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1804161394 Muscat Sultanate of Oman Television Network in 
Arabic 1400 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1804161394 </F>
<F P=104>  Muscat Sultanate of Oman Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The water resources working group within the 
multilateral talks stemming from the Middle East peace 
conference continued its meetings at the Muscat Intercontinental 
Hotel this morning. 
  The sultanate's delegation to this meeting was led by His 
Excellency Muhammad Bin-'Alawi al-Khusaybi, the Omani ambassador 
to Japan. 
  A source close to the meeting said the group will discuss 
the 
same issues on its agenda again today, including regional 
cooperation, administering water resources, and collecting data 
on water and water supplies. 
  The conferees have initially agreed to set up an 
international research center on sea water desalination in the 
sultanate. The center will try to coordinate research efforts 
in order to reduce the costs of sea water desalination 
technology, in order to enable the countries of the region to 
get fresh water at low cost, and to reduce dependence on 
declining quantities of surface and ground waters. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

