<H3> <TI>   Wrapup of Reports on GATT Meetings, Speeches, Results </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Wrapup of Reports on GATT Meetings, Speeches, Results </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Uruguay Round Final Act Signed </H4>

<F P=102> LD1604145994 Rabat MAP in English 1319 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1604145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rabat MAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Marrakech, Apr. 16 (MAP) -- Over one hundred nations 
have laid the foundations of a new world economic order that 
they wished to be more prosperous and just when they adopted 
here Friday the Uruguay round final act on the largest 
liberalization of world trade in history. 
  Morocco, the host country was the first to initial the 
documents and Zimbabwe was the last to append its signature on 
the final act concluding thus a signing ceremony that lasted for 
over four hours and during which the participating countries 
succeeded one another at the signing desk in English 
alphabetical order. 
  Besides the final act, the participating countries also 
signed the accord setting up the World Trade Organization as 
well as three accords on public projects, dairy products and 
bovine meat. 
  The participating countries to the negotiations which have 
not signed the documents Friday in Marrakech can do so in Geneva 
where the GATT is based when they wish. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

