<H3> <TI>   Al-Bashir Clarifies Remarks on Contacts With U.S. Envoy </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Al-Bashir Clarifies Remarks on Contacts With U.S. Envoy </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   EA1804221994 Khartoum SUNA in Arabic 1725 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> EA1804221994 </F>
<F P=104>  Khartoum SUNA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Khartoum, 18 Apr (SUNA) -- The president of the 
Republic, Lieutenant General 'Umar al-Bashir, has said in a 
statement to the AL-MULTAQA magazine that the government had 
earlier stopped its contacts with the American ambassador 
because of its indignation over his hostile statements. These 
came at a time when both sides, the Government of Sudan and the 
American Government, had agreed to resume their dialogue on the 
basis of frankness. 
  It is worth, mentioning that some news agencies had quoted 
the presidents statement imprecisely. 

</TEXT>

