<F P=100> Sudan </F>
<H3> <TI>   Official Comments on Saudi Hajj `Limitations' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Comments on Saudi Hajj `Limitations' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   NC1904104094 Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network in Persian 0330 GMT 19 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> NC1904104094 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran Voice of the Islamic Republic of Iran 
First Program Network </F>

<F P=105>  Persian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The deputy foreign minister of Sudan met with his 
Iranian counterpart in Tehran yesterday. During this meeting, 
the two sides called for the expansion of bilateral relations. 
  The Sudanese deputy foreign minister commented on the 
limitations by the Saudi Government on the quota of pilgrims to 
Mecca and on the need to examine problems faced by the world of 
Islam during the Hajj congress, and emphasized the significance 
of the religious and political aspect of the Hajj pilgrimage. 
The Sudanese deputy foreign minister stated: When the Saudis 
say that the quota for pilgrims from Islamic countries has been 
set by the Islamic Conference Organization, then this 
organization should also make all the decisions concerning the 
Hajj pilgrimage as well. 

</TEXT>

