<H3> <TI>   New Industrial, Restructuring Minister Notes Post </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    New Industrial, Restructuring Minister Notes Post </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1704113494 Algiers Radio Algiers Network in Arabic 0600 
GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1704113494 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers Radio Algiers Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] Mourad Benachnou, the minister of industrial 
restructuring and participation [former economy minister], 
yesterday described his new duty as important. He said it will 
be within the framework of reorganizing the economy on the basis 
of the stability program, which was negotiated with the IMF. 
  Meanwhile, Benachnou affirmed the commitment of the new 
Prime 
Minister Mokdad Sifi to honor Algeria's international pledges. 
He added that without restructuring the economy -- which is the 
second stage of the government's policy after balancing finances 
-- the stability program could never succeed. He said that 
options that accommodate Algeria's social reality should be 
found. 
  The prime minister, who installed Benachnou in his new duty, 
said that the aim of creating this new ministry was to create a 
new nucleus in order to restructure the economy along the path 
of industrial restructuring and crossing into the market 
economy. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

