<F P=100> ARAB AFRICA </F>
<F P=101> Algeria </F>
<H3> <TI>   Security Forces Kill 4 `Terrorists,' Arrest 17 Others </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Security Forces Kill 4 `Terrorists,' Arrest 17 Others </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1604211094 Algiers ENTV Television Network in Arabic 1900 
GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> LD1604211094 </F>
<F P=104>  Algiers ENTV Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A communique of the security services mentioned that 
the terrorist Sayah Atia died last February following injuries 
he sustained during a clash with the security forces. This was 
confirmed by terrorists close to Atia who were arrested by the 
security services. 
  The source pointed out that Sayah Atia, alias El Khan, who 
carried out several assassinations, was seriously injured by 
security forces during a manhunt in the Medea province on 13 
February 1994. 
  The security services announced that their forces were able 
to kill four terrorists and arrest 17 others between last Sunday 
and Thursday in Jijel, Blida, Boumerdes, Tiaret, and Bouira. 
The security forces recovered a Mat 49 pistol stolen during an 
aggression carried out in Lakhdaria in February 1992. 
  On the other hand, the security services pointed out that 
three out of the four terrorists who were killed in Mila 
province on 5 April were identified as being those who escaped 
from the re-education prison of Tazoult on 10 March 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

