in Arabic 1600 GMT 15 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=105> Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Dear listeners, we have just received the following 
statement from the presidential council of the Kurdistan region 
on the destruction of the two helicopters in the airspace of 
Kurdistan: 
  O esteemed citizens, o masses of our struggling people; on 
14 
April, two helicopters belonging to the coalition states, which 
were entrusted with defending the security of Kurdistan, were 
destroyed when they were fired upon by mistake by coalition 
fighter planes. The incident left all the passengers of the two 
helicopters dead. 
  As a sign of our appreciation for their sacrifice and spirit 
of cooperation in the service of human rights and democracy in 
Kurdistan, we have decided to declare a three-day general 
mourning period, effective today, 15 April. Prayers will be 
performed in all mosques and bells will be tolled in all 
churches for this painful event. 
  All media networks in Kurdistan shall comply with this 
decision. 

