<F P=102>   JN1604194194 Baghdad INA in Arabic 1540 GMT 16 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> JN1604194194 </F>
<F P=104>  Baghdad INA </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Baghdad, 16 Apr (INA) -- The Ministry of Justice has 
urged organizations and bodies connected with international law 
and the defense of human rights and freedoms to work toward 
lifting the unjust embargo against Iraq. 
  In cables to these organizations, the Ministry of Justice 
said Iraq has fulfilled its obligations under Section C of 
Security Council Resolution 687. The Security Council should 
therefore implement Paragraph 22 of this resolution and lift the 
embargo imposed on the Iraqi people. The ministry noted that 
the continuation of the embargo is a blatant violation of the 
Universal Declaration of Human Rights and the Geneva Conventions. 

</TEXT>

