<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decision To Close Hamas Offices in Amman Detailed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Decision To Close Hamas Offices in Amman Detailed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PM1804154894 London AL-HAYAH in Arabic 17 Apr 94 pp1, 4 </F>
<F P=103> PM1804154894 </F>
<F P=104>  London AL-HAYAH </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Salamah Ni'mat: "King Husayn Announces Ban on </F>
Hamas Activities"] 
  [Excerpts] Amman -- King Husayn of Jordan yesterday 
announced a ban on the activities of the Islamic Resistance 
Movement (Hamas) in Jordan and emphasized that his country did 
not recognize or deal with any Palestinian organization other 
than the PLO as the sole legitimate representative of the 
Palestinian people. King Husayn, speaking at a press conference 
he held after chairing a cabinet meeting which discussed the 
Israeli threats to the Kingdom and the charge that Jordan 
supports Hamas, said that any Palestinian organization other 
than the PLO would be treated as "unlawful." [passage omitted] 
  Responsible government sources have told AL-HAYAH that the 
government "had decided to close Hamas' offices in Amman" and 
ban its informational activities before Rabin made his threats. 
  The sources pointed out that the government considered that 
step "an internal matter in harmony with Jordan's policy which 
sees the PLO as the only party empowered to speak for the 
Palestinian people." 
  They stressed that the official authorities "have not and 
will not take any measures" against Hamas representative in 
Jordan Muhammad Nazzal or its official spokesman Ibrahim 
Ghawshah, "because the two are Jordanian citizens who abide by 
the country's current Constitution and laws." The same sources 
pointed out that "despite Jordan's affirmation that neither 
Nazzal nor Ghawshah had anything to do with the planning and 
execution of military operations in the occupied territory, we 
will allow no one to exploit their statements in the media to 
undermine Jordan." [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-13241 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drnes075_m_94005" </HT>


