<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Hamas Office `Operational' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hamas Office `Operational' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   TA1904133694 Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ in Hebrew 19 Apr 94 p A3 </F>
<F P=103> TA1904133694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tel Aviv HA'ARETZ </F>
<F P=105>  Hebrew </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Tzvi Bar'el] </F>
  [Text] The Hamas office in Jordan continues functioning 
regularly, despite reports and announcements that it had been 
closed. Office workers come to work, answer phones, and operate 
the office as before. In a telephone conversation with the 
Hamas office, Muhammad Nazzal, head of the movement, said that 
the office exists and is operational, "but unfortunately, I 
cannot make comments to your newspaper because it is our policy 
not to speak with Israeli elements." 
  Jordanian sources in Amman have reported that the king's 
decision regarding Hamas has remained unchanged but, as far as 
they know, no practical steps to restrict the movement's 
activity have been taken so far. According to them, the heads 
of the movement were summoned for a discussion with the heads of 
the Jordanian intelligence who asked that Hamas media activity 
be reduced. 

</TEXT>

