<DATE1>  18 Apr 1994 </DATE1>

</HEADER>

<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Crown Prince Cancels U.S. Visit Due to `Tension' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Crown Prince Cancels U.S. Visit Due to `Tension' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   JN1904120294 Amman AL-MAJD in Arabic 18 Apr 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> JN1904120294 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman AL-MAJD </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Following the U.S.-Jordanian tension resulting from 
the al-'Aqabah Port blockade, Crown Prince Hasan has decided to 
cancel a visit to Washington scheduled 20 April. Jordan had 
expected that the United States would decide to lift the 
blockade against ships bound for al-'Aqabah Port and allow 
inspection of ships at the port instead of accosting them on the 
high seas. 
  Jordan has already conveyed its views to the United States 
and the world and the issue has become clear and does not have 
to be discussed by the prince in Washington during the visit, 
which was scheduled one month before the outbreak of the present 
crisis. Talks during the visit were supposed to focus on certain 
economic aspects and political issues which cannot be discussed 
now before the al-'Aqabah blockade crisis is over. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

