<F P=100> JORDAN </F>
<H3> <TI>   Lebanese Parliament Speaker, Team Pay Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Lebanese Parliament Speaker, Team Pay Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    King Confers With Birri, Comments </H4>

<F P=102> JN1704171894 Amman Jordan Television Network in Arabic 1500 
GMT 17 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> JN1704171894 </F>
<F P=104>  Amman Jordan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Arabic </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] His Majesty King Husayn received at Raghadan Palace 
today Nabih Birri, speaker of the Lebanese Chamber of Deputies, 
and his delegation. The meeting was attended by His Highness 
Crown Prince Hasan. 
  His majesty held a closed meeting, attended by the crown 
prince, with Nabih Birri, followed by an expanded meeting 
attended by a number of officials from both sides. 
  At the outset of the meeting, his majesty welcomed Birri and 
his delegation and emphasized importance of such meetings on all 
legislative and political levels in Arab countries, and the need 
to intensify these meetings in the service of the causes of the 
Arab nation and to lead the nation toward its aspirations. 
  His majesty emphasized the importance of continuous contacts 
between political leaderships and the need to intensify efforts 
in a manner that realizes serious and constructive coordination 
between the Arab countries to the peace process, because this 
continuous coordination is a national and pan-Arab interest to 
which all should adhere. 
  For his part, Birri stressed the appreciation of the 
Lebanese 
people for His majesty King Husayn's pan-Arab and honorable 
positions and his eagerness to support the brotherly Lebanese 
people and the Lebanese leadership in defending the just 
Lebanese cause. He expressed admiration of the wise leadership 
of His Majesty King Husayn and his positions on various crucial 
pan-Arab issues. 
  The meeting was attended by 'Abd-al-Salam al-Majali, prime 
minister; His Excellency al-Sharif Zayd Bin-Shakir, chief of the 
Royal Hashemite Court; Ahmad al-Lawzi, Senate president; Tahir 
al-Masri, speaker of the House of Representatives; advisers of 
his majesty the king; the Jordanian ambassador in Beirut; and 
Deputy 'Abd-al-Hadi al-Majali, head of the Foreign Affairs 
Committee at the House of Representatives. 
  On the Lebanese side, the meeting was attended by Deputy 
Asmar Asmar, Deputy 'Ali Mita, Deputy Astafan al-Duayhi, Deputy 
'Ala' al-Din, and the Lebanese ambassador in Amman. 
  [Begin recording] [Unidentified correspondent] We know how 
much you love Lebanon and its people. What can say after this 
meeting with Speaker Birri and the parliamentary delegation? 
  [Husayn] This meeting is a blessed one. The beloved members 
of the delegation are now in their second homeland, and I am 
happy to have this chance to welcome my brothers. The hopes and 
aspirations of both sides are the same. We are the closest to 
each other among the Arabs. We pray God that henceforth, the 
march of real coordination and cooperation will resume. We have 
great expectations that wider Arab coordination and cooperation 
will take place in these difficult circumstances and in face of 
the challenges. There is much love for Lebanon in the hearts of 
all Jordanians from various origins. We are proud of our 
strong, brotherly, and continuous relations with God's care. 
  [Correspondent] Your Majesty, Speaker Birri described you as 
the most patient Arab leader. How do you view the future of 
this region, especially Lebanon and Jordan? 
  [Husayn] This is nice coming from my brother, and it is an 
honor to me and to Jordan. In fact, these circumstances require 
patience. But on the other hand, we feel that these 
circumstances will not continue in terms of our suffering in the 
whole of the Arab world. Therefore, we are patient and we wait 
for a real awakening and a serious and meaningful Arab move. We 
believe in the Arab individual and that it is inevitable that he 
will have the right to live and will attain all his rights in 
his greater Arab homeland. 
  [Correspondent] Thank you Your Majesty. 
  [Husayn] Thank you. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

