<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   Army Foils Attempt To Smuggle Arms in Kashmir </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Army Foils Attempt To Smuggle Arms in Kashmir </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1804145994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1430 
GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1804145994 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi All India Radio Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Army has foiled yet another bid by Pakistani 
infiltrators to smuggle in a large quantity of arms and 
ammunition through the northern sector into the Kashmir state. 
A Defense Ministry spokesman told newsmen in Srinagar that this 
is the biggest cache of arms recovered so far this year. It 
includes 32,000 rounds of ammunition, 92 hand grenades, 203 
antipersonnel mines and a large quantity of incriminating 
documents. A massive hunt has been launched to trace the arms 
couriers. Meanwhile, security forces launched a huge search 
operation this morning in the Batmalu area and adjoining 
localities to nab militants. 
  Elsewhere in the state, 10 militants have been killed during 
the past 24 hours. Of these three were killed in intergang 
rivalry. 

</TEXT>

