<F P=100> SOUTH ASIA </F>
<F P=101> India </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Dreaded Militant' Among 4 Killed in Punjab </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Dreaded Militant' Among 4 Killed in Punjab </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK1904070594 Delhi Doordarshan Television Network in English 
1630 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK1904070594 </F>
<F P=104>  Delhi Doordarshan Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] In Punjab, dreaded militant Avtar Singh, the deputy 
chief of the Babbar Khalsa, was among four militants killed in 
an encounter in Punjab. A large quantity of arms and ammunition 
was recovered from them. Police officials say the security 
forces cordoned off an area near Sangrur on a tip-off, leading 
to the encounter. Avtar Singh carried an award of 10 lakh 
rupees. Police say the gang led by Avtar Singh was responsible 
for over 100 killings in Punjab. Avtar Singh visited Pakistan 
on numerous occasions and brought back consignments of weapons 
to Punjab. 

</TEXT>

