<H3> <TI>   Sudanese Deputy Foreign Minister Arrives </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sudanese Deputy Foreign Minister Arrives </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD1804182394 Tehran IRNA in English 1700 GMT 18 Apr 94 </F>
<F P=103> LD1804182394 </F>
<F P=104>  Tehran IRNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tehran, April 18, IRNA -- Sudanese Deputy Foreign 
Minister Yusuf 'Umar Baradah arrived here Monday on a three-day 
official stay and was welcomed by his Iranian counterpart 
Mohammad Hashemi at the airport. 
  Talking to reporters upon his arrival, Barideh described 
Tehran-Khartoum ties as "excellent" and said his government was 
for further expansion of the "cordial bilateral relations" in 
various fields. 
  Baradah, who carries a written message from Sudanese Foreign 
Minister Husayn Sulayman Abu-Salih for his Iranian counterpart 
'Ali Akbar Velayati, said Iran and Sudan are the target of 
adverse propaganda for their efforts to implement Islamic laws. 
  He said his government was proud of Iranian and Sudanese 
officials' adoption of an independent political and economic 
path which has led to growing ties between the two countries. 
  Hashemi referred to the age-old cultural, historical and 
religious commonalities between Iran and Sudan and underscored 
expansion of bilateral relations. 

</TEXT>

